text.section:
The Fund consists of:
Money collected from a nonprofit health service plan in accordance with § 14-106.1 of the Insurance Article;
Interest earned on investments;
Money donated to the Fund;
Money awarded to the Fund through grants; and
Any other money from any other source accepted for the benefit of the Fund.

section.section:
The Fund may be used only to:
Cover the administrative costs of the Commission;
Cover the actual documented direct costs of fulfilling the statutory and regulatory duties of the Commission in accordance with the provisions of this subtitle;
Provide operating grants to qualifying community health resources; and
Provide funding for the development, support, and monitoring of a unified data information system among primary and specialty care providers, hospitals, and other providers of services to community health resource members.

text.section:
The Commission shall adopt regulations that:
Establish the criteria for a community health resource to qualify for a grant;
Establish the procedures for disbursing grants to qualifying community health resources;
Develop a formula for disbursing grants to qualifying community health resources;
Establish criteria and mechanisms for funding a unified data information system; and
In consultation with the Secretary, implement a program to provide subsidies to community health resources for office-based specialty care visits, diagnostic testing, and laboratory tests.

In developing regulations under subsection (f)(1) of this section, the Commission shall:
Consider geographic balance; and
Give priority to community health resources that:
In addition to normal business hours, have evening and weekend hours of operation;
Have partnered with a hospital to establish a reverse referral program at the hospital;
Reduce the use of the hospital emergency department for nonemergency services;
Assist patients in establishing a medical home with a community health resource;
Coordinate and integrate the delivery of primary and specialty care services;
Promote the integration of mental and somatic health with federally qualified health centers or other somatic care providers;
Fund medication management or therapy services for uninsured individuals up to 200% of the federal poverty level who meet medical necessity criteria but who are ineligible for the public mental health system;
Provide a clinical home for individuals who access hospital emergency departments for mental health services, substance abuse services, or both; and
Support the implementation of evidence-based clinical practices.
